textBeforeTable: NO. 12 LIMESTONE COLLEGE VS. NO. 16 KING COLLEGE   King will continue its regional play when they travel to Belmont, N.C. to wrestle Belmont Abbey College on Wednesday, Feb. 8 before hosting a tri-meet on Feb. 11 with Ohio Valley and Lake Erie College. Brandon Tressler (Orlando, Fla.) returned to form with a win by decision, defeating Landon Hall (184) by a 6-2 count. Leading 21-13, Frank Morgan (Maynardville, Tenn.) clinched the win with a 10-3 decision over Demetre Ligiori (197), after Limestone decided to sit No. 1 Dan Scanlan. Dondricus Anderson (Macon, Ga.) finalized the meet with a 10-5 decision over Charles Weber, leading to a 27-13 team win over the Saints. Dyvon Passmore (Miami, Fla.) made easy work of Chris Didyoung (174), pinning him 2:02 into the opening period to regain the lead, 18-13. The Tornado never relinquished the advantage and scored nine more insurance points with consecutive wins by decision to close out the meet. After falling behind 6-9, freshman Jeremy Miller (Madison, Tenn.) pulled out a tide-turning win by pinning Brennin Adkins in the second period, 1:29 into the frame to take a 12-9 lead. Limestone retook the lead when Daniel McGillivray won a major decision over John Brasher (McCalla, Ala.) for a 12-13 lead but King won the next four bouts to secure the team victory. Through three bouts the Tornado and Saints were even, 6-6, after decision
